North West Premier Prof Job Mokgoro will on Thursday visit a centre in Mmabatho that was torched during the uprisings in the province in April. The Mmabana Arts and Cultural centre was among buildings that were destroyed, burnt down and looted. When residents of Mahikeng and surrounding areas were calling for the recall of former Premier Supra Mahumapelo. Spokesperson at the Office of Premier Mokgoro, Vuyisile Ngesi says: “He is interested in doing a walkabout to see the damage that has been caused to the buildings and other properties in around Mmabatho.” “You must remember that those are buildings that were damaged and torched during the April uprising in the North West. Therefore the premier wants to see for himself so that when we interact with management and board we are able to quantify the damage.”